45:04.619 --> 45:06.536
You can't lock up a man for 52 days

45:06.621 --> 45:08.914
without him knowing when
or even if he's ever getting out.

45:08.998 --> 45:12.376
You can't lock up a reporter
for protecting his source.

45:12.460 --> 45:14.252
-You can't have everything. And you...
-Rebecca.

45:14.337 --> 45:15.712
I have not yielded the floor.

45:15.797 --> 45:17.631
I won't be contesting your motion.

45:18.466 --> 45:19.841
I'm sorry?

45:20.176 --> 45:23.512
I won't be contesting your motion.
I'll be joining it.

45:24.138 --> 45:26.723
This isn't supposed to be punitive.
It's supposed to be coercive.

45:26.808 --> 45:29.309
And plainly he's not giving up the name.

45:30.228 --> 45:31.728
He'll sleep at home tonight.

45:43.533 --> 45:48.912
Follow me.

45:51.457 --> 45:52.707
Where are we going?

45:52.792 --> 45:54.835
Exactly where you think we're going.

45:54.919 --> 45:57.087
I don't know what... I'm confused.

45:58.506 --> 45:59.756
We're running into turbulence.

45:59.841 --> 46:02.926
You have to go to your seats
and put your seat belts on.

46:03.428 --> 46:04.553
This is awkward.

46:04.637 --> 46:07.222
I was sitting far away from you.
I was watching episode four.

46:07.306 --> 46:09.349
I'm sorry, would you mind trading back?

46:09.434 --> 46:11.268
We're in the middle of turbulence.

46:11.352 --> 46:15.355
It's nothing. It's due to the action
of molecular viscosity called laminar flow.

46:17.066 --> 46:18.400
Okay.

46:19.819 --> 46:22.696
-Where did that come from?
-Sit down. Put on your seat belt.

46:58.858 --> 47:01.651
And we're joined now by Bree Dorrit,
editor of ACN Digital

47:01.736 --> 47:03.445
and father of the ACNgage app.

47:03.529 --> 47:04.946
-Thanks for joining us, Bree.
-Hi, Sloan.

47:05.031 --> 47:08.366
<i>We saw some of it in the package</i>
<i>we just played, but tell us about ACNgage.</i>

47:08.451 --> 47:09.993
<i>It's a map that tells you where celebrities</i>

47:10.077 --> 47:11.828
<i>have been sighted</i>
<i>in New York or Los Angeles.</i>

47:11.913 --> 47:14.206
<i>And soon we'll be</i>
<i>expanding to Vegas and South Beach.</i>

47:14.290 --> 47:17.042
Any time you want, you can scroll
around and see, you know,

47:17.126 --> 47:19.878
Jude Law was shopping for condoms at
Duane Reade on 57th or...

47:19.962 --> 47:23.215
So people are out there and
they can post a message to us and say,

47:23.299 --> 47:25.675
"Kristen Bell and her kid
are at the 4:00 p.m. showing

47:25.760 --> 47:27.511
<i>"of How to Train Your Dragon</i>
at the ArcLight?"

47:27.595 --> 47:29.012
<i>And it goes right on our map,</i>
<i>instantly.</i>

47:29.096 --> 47:31.014
<i>So that when Kristen Bell</i>
<i>and her kid come out of the movies,</i>

47:31.098 --> 47:33.058
there are a dozen sociopaths
waiting for them?

47:35.770 --> 47:37.062
I don't think that's likely.

47:37.146 --> 47:38.688
Why not?

47:38.773 --> 47:41.066
Well, it's the price of fame, isn't it?

47:41.150 --> 47:43.193
<i>No, it's not. It's a punishment for it.</i>

47:43.277 --> 47:45.695
<i>Celebrities have been stalked</i>
<i>and celebrities have been murdered.</i>

47:45.780 --> 47:47.864
What this app is best at
is assisting in that, right?

47:48.491 --> 47:51.326
I'm sorry you feel that way.
ACNgage is citizen journalism.

47:51.786 --> 47:53.370
Can you talk about the vetting process

47:53.454 --> 47:55.539
-the citizen journalism undergoes?
-The vetting?

47:55.623 --> 47:57.374
<i>People can post more than locations.</i>

47:57.458 --> 47:59.292
<i>-They can post observations.</i>
<i>-That's right.</i>

47:59.377 --> 48:01.711
<i>I'm asking if those posts</i>
<i>are fact-checked.</i>

48:01.796 --> 48:03.838
<i>This is one specific element of the site...</i>

48:03.923 --> 48:06.091
<i>For instance, in a post today</i>
<i>a citizen journalist tells us</i>

48:06.175 --> 48:08.426
that Jimmy Kimmel
was visibly intoxicated last night

48:08.511 --> 48:10.053
at the Soho House in West Hollywood.

48:10.137 --> 48:11.137
That's right.

48:11.222 --> 48:13.765
Jimmy Kimmel was with his family
in Cabo San Lucas last night.

48:14.475 --> 48:15.517
Uh...

48:15.601 --> 48:18.311
People don't read this
with the expectation of it being true.

48:18.396 --> 48:20.063
-Everyone...
-Excuse me?

48:20.147 --> 48:21.565
-Everyone...
-People don't have an expectation

48:21.649 --> 48:23.024
that what they're reading is true?

48:23.109 --> 48:24.776
<i>They read it for the immediacy.</i>

48:24.860 --> 48:26.611
<i>But you're using the word journalism,</i>

48:26.696 --> 48:29.239
which means there is an expectation
that what they're reading is true.

48:29.323 --> 48:31.741
But let me take it a step further.
Let's pretend it was true

48:31.826 --> 48:35.662
<i>that Jimmy Kimmel was intoxicated last night</i>
<i>at the Soho House in West Hollywood.</i>

48:35.746 --> 48:37.581
<i>It's not true, but we don't care,</i>
<i>so let's pretend that it is</i>

48:37.665 --> 48:38.999
<i>since that's what we're doing anyway.</i>

48:39.083 --> 48:40.500
<i>Why does that belong on our website?</i>

48:40.585 --> 48:42.252
Leave her on as long as she wants.

48:42.336 --> 48:46.423
Honestly, I think there's a shifting definition
of what's public and private space.

48:46.507 --> 48:47.882
There is, and we should care about that.

48:47.967 --> 48:49.092
But my question is

48:49.176 --> 48:52.262
why should we care about
a talk show host drinking at a bar?

48:52.346 --> 48:55.265
Don't you think it's great that we're
not putting people up on a pedestal

48:55.349 --> 48:56.766
and worshiping them anymore?

48:56.851 --> 49:00.145
I don't think celebrities are
one of the bigger problems facing us,

49:00.229 --> 49:02.355
but aren't we the ones building the pedestal?

49:02.440 --> 49:04.107
You've got a map that gives us their location.

49:04.191 --> 49:06.693
The idea is that we're
acknowledging that they're real people.

49:06.777 --> 49:08.862
I wonder how many of us
didn't already know that.

49:08.946 --> 49:10.780
But you're doing more than
acknowledging they're real people.

49:10.865 --> 49:11.865
You're beating them up for it.

49:12.241 --> 49:15.410
Aren't they protected by the piles of
money they're surrounded by?

49:15.494 --> 49:17.621
Okay, what's the line of demarcation?

49:17.705 --> 49:19.289
You make over X dollars a year

49:19.373 --> 49:21.625
and now you get to be treated by us
as a regular person

49:21.709 --> 49:24.127
who's basically had an electronic bracelet
slapped on their ankle.

49:24.211 --> 49:25.378
What does X equal?

49:25.463 --> 49:27.756
It would be silly to name
an exact dollar amount.

49:27.840 --> 49:29.382
You're paid $55,000 a year.

49:29.467 --> 49:30.884
Well, that's private.

49:30.968 --> 49:34.429
Sorry. That's almost twice the
national average for a family of four.

49:34.513 --> 49:36.598
Do your piles of cash protect
you from this interview

49:36.682 --> 49:39.142
in which I'm intentionally
stripping you of your dignity?

49:39.226 --> 49:42.103
And, by the way,
I've managed to do it without lying once.

49:42.188 --> 49:44.481
So I'm going to give you another
chance to answer my question

49:44.565 --> 49:46.232
before I answer it myself.

49:46.317 --> 49:48.485
What's the value of an unsourced,
unvetted story

49:48.569 --> 49:51.404
about a grown man drinking at a bar?

49:56.994 --> 49:59.663
I can't give you all the time in the world.
It's entertainment.

49:59.747 --> 50:01.206
My concern isn't for the celebrities,

50:01.290 --> 50:04.459
even though as sure as we're sitting here,
someone's gonna get hurt.

50:04.543 --> 50:05.627
My concern is for the rest of us,

50:05.711 --> 50:08.546
who you're turning into
a wild pack of pride-less punks.

50:10.091 --> 50:11.675
That's News Night for June 24th.

50:11.759 --> 50:13.760
I'm Sloan Sabbith filling in for Will McAvoy.

50:13.928 --> 50:16.304
<i>Terry Smith's up next</i>
with The Capitol Report.

50:20.226 --> 50:21.434
We're clear.

50:22.853 --> 50:25.105
Pruit's gonna kill you for this.

50:25.189 --> 50:26.856
I know.

50:32.071 --> 50:34.656
-Did you put her up to that?
-Let's go in my office.

50:34.740 --> 50:37.784
-No! We'll go where I fucking say we go!
-Charlie.

50:37.868 --> 50:40.203
-Did you put her up to it?
-Nobody put me up to anything.

50:40.287 --> 50:41.871
What did you think you were doing?

50:41.956 --> 50:44.332
-You saw the questions she was gonna ask?
-'Course I saw the questions.

50:44.417 --> 50:45.417
I was doing the interview the only way

50:45.501 --> 50:47.252
-that made sense to me.
-You were openly insubordinate!

50:47.336 --> 50:49.045
I was told to do this interview.

50:49.130 --> 50:50.547
You knew what I was looking for!

50:50.631 --> 50:52.549
I did and I didn't like it, but I did it anyway.

50:52.633 --> 50:55.218
-That was my interview.
-I tried to do the best I could, but I didn't...

50:55.302 --> 50:56.803
I'm tired of this.

50:56.887 --> 50:58.471
Did you get the Princeton kid?

50:58.848 --> 51:01.141
Charlie, let's go into my office
and sit down for a minute.

51:01.225 --> 51:02.892
Did you get the Princeton kid?

51:05.688 --> 51:07.689
-No.
-Why not?

51:09.358 --> 51:10.525
Couldn't find her.

51:12.153 --> 51:13.319
You couldn't...

51:14.864 --> 51:15.905
No.

51:15.990 --> 51:18.908
-You couldn't find her?
-No.

51:18.993 --> 51:20.910
Is this a mutiny?

51:20.995 --> 51:22.370
It's an intervention.

51:22.455 --> 51:24.914
I'm trying to keep this together!

51:24.999 --> 51:27.500
Her and her, tell 'em to pack their shit
and get out of here.

51:27.585 --> 51:29.669
-I apologize for the interview.
-I don't.

51:29.754 --> 51:31.755
-Pack up your shit and get out of here, lady.
-Look...

51:31.839 --> 51:34.591
She tore apart our network,
except it isn't ours, it's mine.

51:34.675 --> 51:37.427
So either Thelma and Louise
vacate the premises in the next five minutes

51:37.511 --> 51:40.930
or I will fire
the motherfucking lot of you right now.

51:41.015 --> 51:43.308
No, you won't. 'Cause you can't.

51:43.392 --> 51:44.768
Only I can.

51:44.852 --> 51:47.437
A parting gift from Mrs. Lansing.

51:47.521 --> 51:50.690
Who on her worst day would never...

51:53.819 --> 51:55.945
We need to talk.

51:56.030 --> 51:57.822
You and me, right now, okay?

51:59.366 --> 52:00.867
Upstairs.

52:01.368 --> 52:02.577
Nobody leaves the premises

52:02.661 --> 52:05.663
until we figure out
how to fix this fucking calamity.

52:08.000 --> 52:10.001
I'll be back in a minute.

52:12.880 --> 52:14.756
-Let's meet in my office.
-I'm there.

54:20.174 --> 54:22.342
It's okay. It's over.

54:29.850 --> 54:32.518
Charlie had a heart attack a few hours ago.

54:35.898 --> 54:37.565
He died.
